Instruction Manual





We are an online watch dealer company established since 2015. We only sell genuine articles from Seiko. We don’t sell fake, replica, knockoff watches. Every item is examined with a fine-tooth comb before we even put it on our store. We also use only reputable and credible worldwide shipping companies. We pride ourselves on delivering only the best experience for our customers, because we guarantee the best price and service. 





1.	Do you sell fake/replica watches?


No. All of our watches are 100% genuine products, it comes with the Original box, manual book, and guarantee card.





2.	How long will shipping take?


Shipping times may vary based on where the package is sent. Our process time after you’ve completed payment is 2-3 business days. It usually takes 5-10 days for the package to arrive after we ship it to you. But it depends on the shipping company and your country’s customs regulations.





3.	Can I request to use a specific courier?


Yes, as long as you inform us in advance.





4.	Can I request a specific product/article?


Yes, if you’re looking for products that are not in our listing, feel free to contact us and we will do our best to find it for you.





Thank you

size:
This 40.50 mm model, inspired by the legendary 1957 original, features a stainless steel case and a green dial with rhodium-plated hour markers and “Broad Arrow” hands - all featuring white Super-LumiNova. There is a date window at 6 o’clock, a small seconds subdial at 9 o’clock, and 12-hour and 60-minute chronograph recorders on the subdial at 3 o’clock.





The brushed bezel includes a blackened tachymeter scale, while on the caseback, there is a “Speedmaster ‘57” engraving as well as a flat sapphire crystal with an anti-reflective treatment inside.





The watch is presented on a matching bracelet with OMEGA’s patented comfort release adjustment system, and is driven by the manual-winding OMEGA Co-Axial Master Chronometer Calibre 9906.





FEATURES: Anti‑magnetic, Chronograph, Chronometer, Date, Master Chronometer Certified, Small seconds, Tachymeter, Time zone function

ABOUT


This pre-owned, 2003 Omega Seamaster 300M Mid-Size Quartz 2562.20 is in like new condition. The watch comes in a black generic presentation box with Omega International Warranty card and 1 year warranty from The Watch Village.




All of our watches undergo a thorough inspection of accuracy, functionality and condition to meet our strict standards. Additionally, we check each watch against records to ensure authenticity and ownership status.




Becoming rarer, this mid-sized Seamaster features an iconic wave pattered dial in striking white. Of which is surrounded by an all steel unidirectional diving bezel that is mounted upon a 34.8mm stainless steel case. The watch is then presented on a matching brushed and polished stainless steel bracelet and powered by the Omega 1538 quartz precision movement with end of battery life indicator.

Omega Seamaster 300
CO‑AXIAL MASTER CHRONOMETER 234.30.41.21.01.001
size:
OMEGA first introduced the Seamaster 300 in 1957 - designed especially for divers and professionals who worked underwater. More than 60 years later, the timepiece has been completely upgraded with an enhanced form that is ready for a new generation of adventurers.





This 41 mm stainless steel model includes a black dial and a black oxalic anodized aluminium bezel with its diving scale filled with vintage Super-LumiNova. The recessed hour markers and open numerals feature Super-LumiNova, which is also present on the rhodium-plated hands.





Presented on an ergonomic stainless steel bracelet, this timepiece includes a transparent sapphire crystal caseback, enabling a clear view of the OMEGA Co-Axial Master Chronometer Calibre 8912.
